Place a #pot over medium-low heat with @butter{2%tbsp}. When melted, remove from
the heat.

Reserve 3 tsp of @biscuit crumb{125%g} and set aside. Mix the remaining biscuit
crumb with the melted butter.

Divide the buttery crumb between two #serving bowls{}. Pat the crumb down with
the back of a #spoon to make the base.

Divide the @salted caramel{80%g} sauce over the top of the biscuit base and pop
into the fridge to firm up.

Place a #pan over medium-high heat with the @coconut milk{1%pack}.

Bring to the boil and simmer for ~{1%min}.

Remove from the heat then stir in the @chocolate chips{100%g} (reserve a few
chocolate chips to make eyes for your ghosts) and a pinch of @salt{to taste}.

Allow to sit for ~{1%min}, then stir the coconut milk and chocolate together
until the chocolate is melted and everything is completely combined. Allow to
cool for ~{5%mins}.

Pour the melted chocolate over the biscuit base.

Cover with #cling film{} and pop into the fridge to set. Leave for ~{2-3%hours}
if you want them fully set. You can also eat them immediately or in ~{1%hour}
if you wish.

Just before serving, sprinkle each chocolate pot with the reserved biscuit crumb.

Whip the @creme fraiche{65%g} until thickened slightly. Pop into a #piping bag{}.
Squeeze small dollops of creme fraiche ghosts on top of the chocolate pots.

> Little Chef's TIP: Kids can help to add the chocolate chip eyes.